's daily candle closed at 0.81292, and today's early price action has so far held above that close, suggesting the recovery leg retains some momentum.\n\nThe structure story over the past month is one of a pair grinding higher from a base, punctuated by sharp two-way swings. The 13 July session produced an aggressive push to 0.81492 \u2014 the highest print in the 30-day window \u2014 before sellers drove price back sharply the following day, closing near 0.8093. That rejection established a clear overhead reference. What is notable, however, is that the subsequent pullback found a floor around the 0.8035\u20130.8050 area, broadly consistent with the structure support zone at 0.80332 which has registered two prior touches. Each time price has approached that level, buyers have reasserted themselves, and the current advance from the 15 July low of 0.80349 is the clearest expression of that dynamic yet. The deeper support zones \u2014 the prior reaction zones at 0.7909, 0.78466, and 0.77776 \u2014 remain well removed from current price and are not in immediate play, though they frame the broader longer-term floor beneath the pair.\n\nOn the H1 timeframe, the picture is orderly and quietly bullish. The overnight Asian session saw a steady grind from the 0.8107 area up through 0.8126, with the 00:00 candle marking the most decisive hourly push. Since then, price has consolidated in a tight 0.8124\u20130.8133 band across the London session, with no meaningful attempt to retest lower. The absence of selling pressure at these levels, combined with higher hourly lows since the early hours, gives the intraday read a constructive tone. The 0.8124\u20130.8126 area has become near-term intraday structure support on the H1.\n\nThe calendar is empty for today, which removes the prospect of sharp event-driven volatility. In the absence of macro catalysts, price action is likely to remain technically driven, with the 0.81337\u20130.81393 prior high cluster acting as the immediate overhead reference. A clean, sustained break and close above that zone on the daily chart would materially strengthen the bullish read and open the path toward a retest of the 0.81492 spike high.\n\nThe read shifts if price reverses and loses the 0.8100 area on a closing basis, which would suggest the recovery is stalling. A daily close back beneath 0.8085 would bring the broader consolidation range back into focus and call the near-term bullish thesis into question.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}